The paper discusses the systematic derivation of a domain-specific transformation language from a given textual modeling language, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of transformation operators, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the usefulness of the derived transformation language in refactoring, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on maintaining and evolving models suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
